    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Single stationary hangings at the head of a bed, generally matching the bed curtains. For side curtains at the upper end of a bed, use "head curtains."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000009761/Cooke, Upholstery in American and Europe (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Colgadura simple fija a la cabecera de una cama, generalmente hace juego con el tornalecho. Para cortinas laterales al extremo superior de una cama, use "cortina de la cabecera."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Enkelvoudige, vaste bedbehangsels aan het hoofdeinde van een bed, doorgaans passend bij de bedgordijnen. Gebruik 'head curtains' voor gordijnen aan beide zijden van het hoofdeinde van een bed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drappo pregiato che si appendeva sulla sommità della testiera del letto, o dietro ad essa appesa al muro; nel Trecento questo termine fu usato anche con significato di stoffe ornamentali appese alle pareti come gli arazzi</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
